  "prompt": "Does the law differentiate between intentional and unintentional money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, the law generally differentiates between intentional and unintentional money laundering. Intentional money laundering typically involves deliberate actions to conceal the source of funds, while unintentional money laundering may result from negligence or lack of proper due diligence. The penalties and legal consequences can vary significantly based on intent.\n\nIntentional money laundering is usually treated as a criminal offense with more severe penalties, potentially including:\n- Substantial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Criminal prosecution\n\nUnintentional money laundering might result in:\n- Civil penalties\n- Regulatory sanctions\n- Required corrective actions\n- Potential fines, but typically less severe\n\nThe specific treatment depends on jurisdiction and circumstances, but intent is a key factor in determining legal consequences.",
